Architecture plan for miketang84-forum002

Stack
- Rust binary crate using Axum + Tokio.
- PostgreSQL via sqlx with checked migrations in `migrations/`.
- Server-rendered HTML via Askama templates.
- Tailwind CSS compiled to static assets served by Axum.
- Cookie-based sessions stored in PostgreSQL.
- Tracing for structured logs and request spans.
- Docker for local/dev deployment parity.

Proposed file/module structure
- `Cargo.toml`: dependencies, features, build profiles.
- `src/main.rs`: bootstrap, config loading, tracing init, router assembly, server startup.
- `src/lib.rs`: shared exports for app construction and tests.
- `src/app.rs`: `build_router(state)` and route registration.
- `src/state.rs`: `AppState` with config, db pool, session store, clock helpers.
- `src/config.rs`: environment-backed config structs and parsing.
- `src/error.rs`: app error enum, HTTP mapping, template-friendly error responses.
- `src/db/mod.rs`: pool creation, migration startup hook, shared query helpers.
- `src/models/`: `user.rs`, `session.rs`, `category.rs`, `thread.rs`, `post.rs`.
- `src/auth/`: password hashing, login/register services, session cookie middleware, guards, current-user extractor, roles.
- `src/web/`: route handlers grouped by domain.
- `src/web/pages/`: `home.rs`, `auth.rs`, `categories.rs`, `threads.rs`, `posts.rs`, `profile.rs`, `admin.rs`, `search.rs`.
- `src/web/middleware/`: request id/logging, csrf, auth/session attach.
- `src/web/forms/`: form payload structs and validation helpers.
- `src/templates/`: Askama templates with `layout.html`, partials, and page templates.
- `src/static/`: compiled CSS target, JS if needed, images/icons.
- `migrations/`: one migration per schema/index concern; no combined mega-migrations.
- `tests/`: integration tests by flow area with shared test harness.
- `scripts/`: seed/bootstrap helpers if shell or Rust helper binaries are needed.
- `docker/` or repo root Docker files: `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`.

Shared types and conventions
- `AppState` wrapped in `Arc`, injected through Axum state.
- `CurrentUser` extractor carrying `user_id`, `username`, and `role`.
- `Role` enum in code mirrored to DB constraint/enum representation.
- `Pagination` helper for page/per-page parsing reused by category/thread/search pages.
- `FlashMessage` or simple query/cookie-based status messaging for auth and admin actions.
- `CsrfToken` helper stored in session and validated on mutating HTML form posts.
- `AppError` centralizes DB, auth, validation, not-found, forbidden, and template errors.
- Plain service functions separate from handlers where behavior is reused by web and tests.

Database shape
- `users`: id, username, email if desired, password_hash, role, bio, timestamps.
- `sessions`: id, user_id, csrf_token, expires_at, created_at, last_seen_at.
- `categories`: id, slug, name, description, sort_order, timestamps.
- `threads`: id, category_id, author_id, title, body/search columns, pinned, locked, timestamps.
- `posts`: id, thread_id, author_id, body/search columns, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at nullable only if soft-delete is later needed.
- Search: `tsvector` columns on threads/posts plus GIN indexes.

Template/UI organization
- Base layout with nav, flash area, search box, and content blocks.
- Shared partials for pagination, form errors, and moderator/admin badges/actions.
- Keep rendering logic thin in templates; prepare view models in handlers.
- Post bodies rendered as escaped plain text with newline-to-`<br>` conversion at presentation edge only.

Testing strategy
- `tests/support/` for test app factory, ephemeral database setup, fixture users, login helpers, and HTML assertions.
- Integration-first coverage for auth, posting, moderation, and CSRF behavior.
- Prefer building app via exported `build_router`/`app_state` helpers so tests use real middleware.

