Key design decisions
- Use SSR-only Axum + Askama instead of client-heavy frontend code to keep issue scope small and testable.
- Keep route handlers thin; put auth/session/posting logic into service-style functions to reduce duplication.
- Use DB-backed sessions so logout, CSRF, and admin invalidation remain server-controlled.
- Model roles explicitly (`user`, `moderator`, `admin`) and enforce them in extractors/guards, not ad hoc in handlers.
- Prefer one-way migrations and additive schema changes; avoid rewriting earlier migrations once issues start landing.
- Use real PostgreSQL in integration tests with migrations applied, because sqlx/session/tsvector behavior is DB-specific.
- Keep initial schema conservative and extend with explicit migrations when search and moderation features arrive.
